    "notes": "This metadata schema supports:\n- Basic emotion labels (emotion)\n- Dimensional emotion model (valence, arousal)\n- DAiW 6×6×6 emotion thesaurus (node_id for 216 emotion nodes)\n- Intensity tiers (0-5 for subtle to overwhelming)\n- Musical intent (key, tempo, mode, chord_progression, groove_type)\n- Performance attributes (swing_ratio, articulation, dynamic_range)\n- Quality metadata (quality_score, rule_breaks, tags, notes)\n\nFor ThesaurusLoader integration:\n- node_id maps to EmotionNode in the 6×6×6 hierarchy (0-215)\n- See python/penta_core/ml/datasets/thesaurus_loader.py for node structure\n- Each node has base_emotion → sub_emotion → sub_sub_emotion hierarchy\n\nFor emotional attributes:\n- valence: -1 (very negative) to +1 (very positive)\n- arousal: 0 (very calm) to 1 (very energetic)\n- intensity_tier: 0-5 (subtle, mild, moderate, strong, intense, overwhelming)\n\nFor rule breaking (intentional music theory violations):\n- See music_brain/session/intent_schema.py for full list\n- Examples: HARMONY_ModalInterchange, RHYTHM_ConstantDisplacement, etc.\n- Used to teach models about intentional emotional expression"
